definitions.definition: A stick or rod used to measure the depth of a liquid . Often used to check the level at which a liquid in an opaque or inaccessible tank or reservoir stands; gauge .
examples: I haven't checked the oil level of my car's motor since I lost the dipstick three months ago.

definitions.definition: An exciseman or supervisor who measures with a dipstick.
A useless person of inferior intellect ; a dipshit .
examples: That referee is a right dipstick .
